---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SqueezyAgent Roadmap"
  description="The evolving pre-v0 roadmap for SqueezyAgent."
  active="roadmap"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">evolving roadmap</span>
      <h1>Bold vision. Honest status.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        SqueezyAgent will not pretend the product is done before v0. This page is
        the draft contract: what is being built, what is not yet proven, and what
        needs evidence before it becomes a public claim.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="roadmap">
      <article class="roadmap-item">
        <span class="status-pill">now</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Foundation and product shape</h3>
          <p>
            Rust implementation, TUI foundation, OpenAI Responses streaming,
            Anthropic Messages streaming, bounded fallback tools, web access
            policy, output receipts, validation harness tasks, and design docs.
            Graph-backed navigation remains the core v0 work.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="roadmap-item">
        <span class="status-pill">v0 target</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Rust semantic navigation</h3>
          <p>
            Tree-sitter Rust parser, local semantic graph, symbol lookup,
            references, call candidates, test pairing, impact queries, and
            targeted span reads.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="roadmap-item">
        <span class="status-pill">v0 target</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Cost machinery</h3>
          <p>
            Receipt-backed read dedup, aggregate tool-result budgets, compact
            evidence packets, provider-aware cost estimates, and visible spend
            summaries.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="roadmap-item">
        <span class="status-pill">proof</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Benchmark receipts</h3>
          <p>
            Deterministic harness runs already support mock OpenAI, mock
            Anthropic, and grep-baseline tasks in CI. Public cost claims should
            wait for live receipt traces with tool calls, files read, tokens,
            wall-clock, and correctness.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="roadmap-item">
        <span class="status-pill">release</span>
        <div>
          <h3>macOS and Linux artifacts</h3>
          <p>
            v0 targets macOS and Linux. Linux release artifacts are planned as
            statically linked musl binaries so they do not depend on glibc.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="roadmap-item">
        <span class="status-pill">later</span>
        <div>
          <h3>More languages and adapters</h3>
          <p>
            Python and framework-aware navigation after the Rust proof works.
            Unsupported languages remain explicit fallbacks, not silent guesses.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
